obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (40761)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40761&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Architects Act, 1972.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 2nd April, 1973, vide notification No. G.S.R. 400(E), dated 16th March, 1973, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (40762)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40762&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "architect" means a person whose name is for the time being entered in the register;`
  line
  line `(b) "Council" means the Council of Architecture constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Indian Institute of Architects" means the Indian Institute of Architects registered under the`
  line `Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(d) "recognised qualification" means any qualification in architecture for the time being included`
  line `in the Schedule or notified under section 15;`
  line
  line `(e) "register" means the register of architects maintained under section 23;`
  line
  line `(f) "regulation" means a regulation made under this Act by the Council;`
  line
  line `(g) "rule" means a rule made under this Act by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (40763)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of Council of Architecture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40763&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, constitute, with effect from such date as may be specified in the notification, a`
  line `Council to be known as the Council of Architecture, which shall be a body corporate, having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and`
  line `immovable, and to contract, and may by that name sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(2) The Head Office of the Council shall be at Delhi or at such other place as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) five architects possessing recognised qualifications elected by the Indian Institute of`
  line `Architects from among its members;`
  line
  line `(b) two persons nominated by the All India Council for Technical Education established by the`
  line `Resolution of the Government of India in the late Ministry of Education No. F.16-10/44-E. III, dated`
  line `the 30th November, 1945;`
  line
  line `(c) five persons elected from among themselves by heads of architectural institutions in India`
  line `imparting full-time instruction for recognised qualifications;`
  line
  line `(d) the Chief Architects in the Ministries of the Central Government to which the Government`
  line `business relating to defence and railways has been allotted and the head of the Architectural`
  line `Organisation in the Central Public Works Department, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one person nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) an architect from each State nominated by the Government of that State;`
  line
  line `(g) two persons nominated by the Institution of Engineers (India) from among its members; and`
  line
  line `(h) one person nominated by the Institution of Surveyors of India from among its members.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Institution of Engineers (India)" means the Institution of Engineers (India) first registered`
  line `in 1920 under the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913) and subsequently incorporated by a Royal`
  line `Charter in 1935;`
  line
  line `(b) "Institution of Surveyors of India" means the Institution of Surveyors registered under the`
  line `Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (a) of sub-section (3), the Central Government may,`
  line `pending the preparation of the register, nominate to the first Council, in consultation with the Indian`
  line `Institute of Architects, persons referred to in the said clause (a) who are qualified for registration under`
  line `section 25, and the persons so nominated shall hold office for such period as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (f) of sub-section (3), the Central Government may,`
  line `pending the preparation of the register, nominate to the first Council, in consultation with the State`
  line `Governments concerned, persons referred to in the said clause (f), who are qualified for registration under`
  line `section 25, and the persons so nominated shall hold office for such period as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (40764)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `President and Vice-President of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40764&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President and the Vice-President of the`
  line `Council shall be elected by the members of the Council from among themselves:`
  line
  line `Provided that on the first constitution of the Council and until the President is elected, a member of`
  line `the Council nominated by the Central Government in this behalf shall discharge the functions of the`
  line President.
  line
  line `(2) An elected President or Vice-President of the Council shall hold office for a term of three years or`
  line `till he ceases to be a member of the Council, whichever is earlier, but subject to his being a member of the`
  line `Council, he shall be eligible for re-election:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) the President or the Vice-President may, by writing under his hand addressed to the`
  line `Vice-President or the President, as the case may be, resign his office;`
  line
  line `(b) the President or the Vice-President shall, notwithstanding the expiry of his term of three years,`
  line `continue to hold office until his successor enters upon office.`
  line
  line `(3) The President and the Vice-President of the Council shall exercise such powers and discharge`
  line `such duties as may be prescribed by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (40765)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Mode of elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40765&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Elections under this Chapter shall be conducted in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any dispute arises regarding any such election, the matter shall be referred by the Council`
  line `to a Tribunal appointed by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette in this behalf,`
  line `and the decision of the Tribunal shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such reference shall be made except on an application made to the Council by an`
  line `aggrieved party within thirty days from the date of the declaration of the result of the election.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses of the Tribunal shall be borne by the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (40766)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Terms of office and casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40766&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, an elected or`
  line `nominated member shall hold office for a term of three years from the date of his election or nomination`
  line `or until his successor has been duly elected or nominated, whichever is later.`
  line
  line `(2) An elected or nominated member may, at any time, resign his membership by writing under his`
  line `hand addressed to the President, or in his absence, to the Vice-President, and the seat of such member`
  line `shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(3) A member shall be deemed to have vacated his seat--`
  line
  line `(i) if he is absent without excuse, sufficient in the opinion of the Council, from three consecutive`
  line `ordinary meetings of the Council; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if he ceases to be a member of the body referred to in clause (a), clause (g) or clause (h) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 3 by which he was elected or nominated, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case where he has been elected under clause (c) of sub-section (3) of section 3, if he`
  line `ceases to hold his appointment as the head of an institution referred to in the said clause.`
  line
  line `(4) A casual vacancy in the Council shall be filled by fresh election or nomination, as the case may`
  line `be, and the person so elected or nominated to fill the vacancy shall hold office only for the remainder of`
  line `the term for which the member whose place he takes was elected or nominated.`
  line
  line `(5) Members of the Council shall be eligible for re-election or re-nomination, but not exceeding three`
  line `consecutive terms.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (40806)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Validity of act or proceeding of Council, Executive Committee or other committees not to be invalidated by reason of vacancy, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40806&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Council or the Executive`
  line `Committee or any other committee shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Council, the Executive Committee or any`
  line `other committee, or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the election or nomination of a person acting as a member thereof, or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (40768)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Disabilities.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40768&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be eligible for election or nomination as a member of the`
  line `Council, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted by a court in India for any offence and sentenced to imprisonment for not`
  line `less than two years, and shall continue to be ineligible for a further period of five years since his`
  line release.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (40769)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Meetings of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40769&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall meet at least once in every six months at such time`
  line `and place and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings`
  line `as may be prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise prescribed by regulations, nine members of the Council shall form a quorum,`
  line `and all the acts of the Council shall be decided by a majority of the members present and voting.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of an equal division of votes, the President, or in his absence, the Vice-President or, in`
  line `the absence of both, the member presiding over the meeting, shall have and exercise a second or casting`
  line vote.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (40770)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Executive Committee and other committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40770&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall constitute from among its`
  line `members an Executive Committee, and may also constitute other committees for such general or special`
  line `purposes as the Council deems necessary to carry out its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee shall consist of the President and the Vice-President of the Council who`
  line `shall be members ex officio and five other members who shall be elected by the Council from among its`
  line members.
  line
  line `(3) The President and the Vice-President of the Council shall be the Chairman and Vice-Chairman`
  line `respectively of the Executive Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) A member of the Executive Committee shall hold office as such until the expiry of his term as a`
  line `member of the Council but subject to his being a member of the Council, he shall be eligible for`
  line re-election.
  line
  line `(5) In addition to the powers and duties conferred and imposed on it by this Act, the Executive`
  line `Committee shall exercise such powers and discharge such duties as may be prescribed by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (40771)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Fees and allowances to President, Vice-President and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40771&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The President, the`
  line `Vice-President and other members of the Council shall be entitled to such fees and allowances as the`
  line `Council may, with the previous sanction of the Central Government, fix in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (40772)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Officers and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40772&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint a Registrar who shall act as its Secretary and who may also act, if so decided by the`
  line `Council, as its treasurer;`
  line
  line `(b) appoint such other officers and employees as the Council deems necessary to enable it to carry`
  line `out its functions under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) with the previous sanction of the Central Government, fix the pay and allowances and other`
  line `conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (a) of sub-section (1), for the first three years from`
  line `the first constitution of the Council, the Registrar of the Council shall be a person appointed by the`
  line `Central Government, who shall hold office during the pleasure of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) All the persons appointed under this section shall be the employees of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (40773)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Finances of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40773&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be established a Fund under the management and control`
  line `of the Council into which shall be paid all moneys received by the Council and out of which shall be met`
  line `all expenses and liabilities properly incurred by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may invest any money for the time being standing to the credit of the Fund in any`
  line `Government security or in any other security approved by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall keep proper accounts of the Fund distinguishing capital from revenue.`
  line
  line `(4) The annual accounts of the Council shall be subject to audit by an auditor to be appointed`
  line `annually by the Council.`
  line
  line `(5) As soon as may be practicable at the end of each year, but not later than the thirtieth day of`
  line `September of the year next following, the Council shall cause to be published in the Official Gazette a`
  line `copy of the audited accounts and the report of the Council for that year and copies of the said accounts`
  line `and report shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The Fund shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys received from the Central Government by way of grant, gift or deposit;`
  line
  line `(b) any sums received under this Act whether by way of fee or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(7) All moneys standing at the credit of Council which cannot immediately be applied shall be`
  line `deposited in the State Bank of India or in any other bank specified in column 2 of the First Schedule to`
  line `the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (40774)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Recognition of qualifications granted by authorities in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40774&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The qualifications included`
  line `in the Schedule or notified under section 15 shall be recognised qualifications for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any authority in India which grants an architectural qualification not included in the Schedule`
  line `may apply to the Central Government to have such qualification recognised, and the Central Government,`
  line `after consultation with the Council, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Schedule so as`
  line `to include such qualification therein, and any such notification may also direct that an entry shall be made`
  line `in the Schedule against such architectural qualification declaring that it shall be a recognised qualification`
  line `only when granted after a specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that until the first Council is constituted, the Central Government shall, before issuing any`
  line `notification as aforesaid, consult an expert committee consisting of three members to be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (40775)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Recognition of architectural qualifications granted by authorities in foreign countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40775&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after consultation with the Council, direct, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, that an architectural qualification granted by any university or other institution in`
  line `any country outside India in respect of which a scheme of reciprocity for the recognition of architectural`
  line `qualification is not in force, shall be a recognised qualification for the purposes of this Act or, shall be so`
  line `only when granted after a specified date or before a specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that until the first Council is constituted the Central Government shall, before issuing any`
  line `notification as aforesaid, consult the expert committee set up under the proviso to sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 14.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may enter into negotiations with the authority in any State or country outside India,`
  line `which by the law of such State or country is entrusted with the maintenance of a register of architects, for`
  line `settling of a scheme of reciprocity for the recognition of architectural qualifications, and in pursuance of`
  line `any such scheme, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that such`
  line `architectural qualification as the Council has decided should be recognised, shall be deemed to be a`
  line `recognised qualification for the purposes of this Act, and any such notification may also direct that such`
  line `architectural qualification shall be so recognised only when granted after a specified date or before a`
  line `specified date.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (40776)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power of Central Government to amend Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40776&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 14, the Central Government, after consultation with the Council, may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Schedule by directing that an entry be made therein in`
  line `respect of any architectural qualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (40777)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Effect of recognition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40777&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, but subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, any recognised qualification shall be a sufficient qualification for enrolment in the`
  line register.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (40778)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to require information as to courses of study and examinations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40778&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every authority in`
  line `India which grants a recognised qualification shall furnish such information as the Council may, from`
  line `time to time, require as to the courses of study and examinations to be undergone in order to obtain such`
  line `qualification, as to the ages at which such courses of study and examinations are required to be undergone`
  line `and such qualification is conferred and generally as to the requisites for obtaining such qualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (40779)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Inspection of examinations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40779&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Executive Committee shall, subject to regulations, if any,`
  line `made by the Council, appoint such number of inspectors as it may deem requisite to inspect any college`
  line `or institution where architectural education is given or to attend any examination held by any college or`
  line `institution for the purpose of recommending to the Central Government recognition of architectural`
  line `qualifications granted by that college or institution.`
  line
  line `(2) The inspectors shall not interfere with the conduct of any training or examination, but shall report`
  line `to the Executive Committee on the adequacy of the standards of architectural education including staff,`
  line `equipment, accommodation, training and such other facilities as may be prescribed by regulations for`
  line `giving such education or on the sufficiency of every examination which they attend.`
  line
  line `(3) The Executive Committee shall forward a copy of such report to the college or institution and`
  line `shall also forward copies with remarks, if any, of the college or institution thereon, to the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (40780)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Withdrawal of recognition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40780&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) When upon report by the Executive Committee it appears to`
  line `the Council--`
  line
  line `(a) that the courses of study and examination to be undergone in, or the proficiency required from`
  line `the candidates at any examination held by, any college or institution, or`
  line
  line `(b) that the staff, equipment, accommodation, training and other facilities for staff and training`
  line `provided in such college or institution,`
  line
  line `do not conform to the standards prescribed by regulations, the Council shall make a representation to that`
  line `effect to appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) After considering such representation the appropriate Government shall forward it along with such`
  line `remarks as it may choose to make to the college or institution concerned, with an intimation of the period`
  line `within which the college or institution, as the case may be, may submit its explanation to the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of the explanation or where no explanation is submitted within the period fixed, then`
  line `on the expiry of that period, the State Government, in respect of the college or institution referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (5), shall make its recommendations to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government--`
  line
  line `(a) after making such further enquiry, if any, as it may think fit, in respect of the college or`
  line `institution referred to in sub-section (3), or`
  line
  line `(b) on receipt of the explanation from a college or institution referred to in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (5), or where no explanation is submitted within the period fixed, then on the expiry of`
  line `that period,`
  line
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that an entry shall be made in the Schedule against the`
  line `architectural qualification awarded by such college or institution, as the case may be, declaring that it`
  line `shall be a recognised qualification only when granted before a specified date and the Schedule shall be`
  line `deemed to be amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section, "appropriate government" means--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to any college or institution established by an Act of Parliament or managed,`
  line `controlled or financed by the Central Government, the Central Government, and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (40781)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Minimum standard of architectural education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40781&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Council may prescribe the minimum`
  line `standards of architectural education required for granting recognised qualifications by colleges or`
  line `institutions in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (40782)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Professional conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40782&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may by regulations prescribe standards of professional`
  line `conduct and etiquette and a code of ethics for architects.`
  line
  line `(2) Regulations made by the Council under sub-section (1) may specify which violations thereof shall`
  line `constitute infamous conduct in any professional respect, that is to say, professional misconduct, and such`
  line `provision shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (40783)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Preparation and maintenance of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40783&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, as soon as may`
  line `be, cause to be prepared in the manner hereinafter provided a register of architects for India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall upon its constitution assume the duty of maintaining the register in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The register shall include the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the full name with date of birth, nationality and residential address of the architect;`
  line
  line `(b) his qualification for registration, and the date on which he obtained that qualification and the`
  line `authority which conferred it;`
  line
  line `(c) the date of his first admission to the register;`
  line
  line `(d) his professional address; and`
  line
  line `(e) such further particulars as may be prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (40784)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `First preparation of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40784&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of preparing the register of architects for the`
  line `first time, the Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a Registration`
  line `Tribunal consisting of three persons who have, in the opinion of the Central Government, the knowledge`
  line `of, or experience in, architecture; and the Registrar appointed under section 12 shall act as Secretary of`
  line `the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, by the same or a like notification, appoint a date on or before`
  line `which application for registration, which shall be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed by rules,`
  line `shall be made to the Registration Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registration Tribunal shall examine every application received on or before the appointed day`
  line `and if it is satisfied that the applicant is qualified for registration under section 25, shall direct the entry of`
  line `the name of the applicant in the register.`
  line
  line `(4) The first register so prepared shall thereafter be published in such manner as the Central`
  line `Government may direct and any person aggrieved by a decision of the Registration Tribunal expressed or`
  line `implied in the register so published may, within thirty days from the date of such publication, appeal`
  line `against such decision to an authority appointed by the Central Government in this behalf by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) The authority appointed under sub-section (4) shall, after giving the person affected an`
  line `opportunity of being heard and after calling for relevant records, make such order as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(6) The Registrar shall amend, where necessary, the register in accordance with the decisions of the`
  line `authority appointed under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(7) Every person whose name is entered in the register shall be issued a certificate of registration in`
  line `such form as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(8) Upon the constitution of the Council, the register shall be given into its custody, and the Central`
  line `Government may direct that the whole or any specified part of the application fees for registration in the`
  line `first register shall be paid to the credit of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (40785)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Qualification for entry in register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40785&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be entitled on payment of such fee as may`
  line `be prescribed by rules to have his name entered in the register, if he resides or carries on the profession of`
  line `architect in India and--`
  line
  line `(a) holds a recognised qualification, or`
  line
  line `(b) does not hold such a qualification but, being a citizen of India, has been engaged in practice as`
  line `an architect for a period of not less than five years prior to the date appointed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 24, or`
  line
  line `(c) possesses such other qualifications as may be prescribed by rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person other than a citizen of India shall be entitled to registration by virtue of a`
  line qualification--
  line
  line `(a) recognised under sub-section (1) of section 15 unless by the law and practice of a country`
  line `outside India to which such person belongs, citizens of India holding architectural qualification`
  line `registrable in that country are permitted to enter and practise the profession of architect in such`
  line `country, or`
  line
  line `(b) unless the Central Government has, in pursuance of a scheme of reciprocity or otherwise,`
  line `declared that qualification to be a recognised qualification under sub-section (2) of section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (40786)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Procedure for subsequent registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40786&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the date appointed for the receipt of`
  line `applications for registration in the first register of architects, all applications for registration shall be`
  line `addressed to the Registrar of the Council and shall be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed by`
  line rules.
  line
  line `(2) If upon such application the Registrar is of opinion that the applicant is entitled to have his name`
  line `entered in the register he shall enter thereon the name of the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person, whose name has under the provisions of this Act been removed from the`
  line `register, shall be entitled to have his name re-entered in the register except with the approval of the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(3) Any person whose application for registration is rejected by the Registrar may, within three`
  line `months of the date of such rejection, appeal to the Council.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon entry in the register of a name under this section, the Registrar shall issue a certificate of`
  line `registration in such form as may be prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (40787)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Renewal fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40787&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct`
  line `that for the retention of a name in the register after the 31st day of December of the year following the`
  line `year in which the name is first entered in the register, there shall be paid annually to the Council such`
  line `renewal fee as may be prescribed by rules and where such direction has been made, such renewal fee shall`
  line `be due to be paid before the first day of April of the year to which it relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the renewal fee is not paid before the due date, the Registrar shall remove the name of the`
  line `defaulter from the register:`
  line
  line `Provided that a name so removed may be restored to the register on, such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) On payment of the renewal fee, the Registrar shall, in such manner as may be prescribed by rules,`
  line `endorse the certificate of registration accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (40788)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Entry of additional qualification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40788&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `An architect shall, on payment of such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules, be entitled to have entered in the register any further recognised qualification which`
  line `he may obtain.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (40789)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Removal from register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40789&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, by order, remove from the register the name of`
  line `any architect--`
  line
  line `(a) from whom a request has been received to that effect, or`
  line
  line `(b) who has died since the last publication of the register.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this section, the Council may order that the name of any architect shall`
  line `be removed from the register where it is satisfied, after giving him a reasonable opportunity of being`
  line `heard and after such further inquiry, if any, as it may think fit to make,`
  line
  line `(a) that his name has been entered in the register by error or on account of misrepresentation or`
  line `suppression of a material fact; or`
  line
  line `(b) that he has been convicted of any offence which, in the opinion of the Council, involves moral`
  line `turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) that he is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(d) that he has been adjudged by a competent court to be of unsound mind.`
  line
  line `(3) An order under sub-section (2) may direct that any architect whose name is ordered to be removed`
  line `from the register shall be ineligible for registration under this Act for such period as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) An order under sub-section (2) shall not take effect until the expiry of three months from the date`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (40790)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Procedure in inquiries relating to misconduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40790&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) When on receipt of a complaint made to it,`
  line `the Council is of opinion that any architect has been guilty of professional misconduct which, if proved,`
  line `will render him unfit to practice as an architect, the Council may hold an inquiry in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(2) After holding the inquiry under sub-section (1) and after hearing the architect, the Council may,`
  line `by order, reprimand the said architect or suspend him from practice as an architect or remove his name`
  line `from the register or pass such other order as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (40791)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Surrender of certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40791&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `A person whose name has been removed from the register under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 27, sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 29 or sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 30, or where such person is dead, his legal representative, as defined in clause (11) of section 2 of`
  line `the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), shall forthwith surrender his certificate of registration to`
  line `the Registrar, and the name so removed shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (40792)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Restoration to register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40792&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Council may, at any time, for reasons appearing to it to be`
  line `sufficient and subject to the approval of the Central Government, order that upon payment of such fee as`
  line `may be prescribed by rules, the name of the person removed from the register shall be restored thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (40793)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Issue of duplicate certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40793&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Where it is shown to the satisfaction of the Registrar that a`
  line `certificate of registration has been lost or destroyed, the Registrar may, on payment of such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules, issue a duplicate certificate in the form prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (40794)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Printing of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40794&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the 1st day of April in each year, the Registrar`
  line `shall cause to be printed copies of the register as it stood on the said date and such copies shall be made`
  line `available to persons applying therefor on payment of such fee as may be prescribed by rules and shall be`
  line `evidence that on that said date the persons whose names are entered therein were architects.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (40795)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Effect of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40795&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any reference in any law for the time being in force to an architect`
  line `shall be deemed to be a reference to an architect registered under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) After the expiry of two years from the date appointed under sub-section (2) of section 24, a person`
  line `who is registered in the register shall get preference for appointment as an architect under the Central or`
  line `State Government or in any other local body or institution which is supported or aided from the public or`
  line `local funds or in any institution recognised by the Central or State Government`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (40796)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Penalty for falsely claiming to be registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40796&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `If any person whose name is not for the time`
  line `being entered in the register falsely represents that it is so entered, or uses in connection with his name or`
  line `title any words or letters reasonably calculated to suggest that his name is so entered, he shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (40797)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Prohibition against use of title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40797&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the expiry of one year from the date appointed under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 24, no person other than a registered architect, or a firm of architects shall use`
  line `the title and style of architect:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this section shall not apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) practice of the profession of an architect by a person designated as a "landscape architect" or`
  line `"naval architect";`
  line
  line `(b) a person who, carrying on the profession of an architect in any country outside India,`
  line `undertakes the function as a consultant or designer in India for a specific project with the prior`
  line `permission of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of clause (a),--`
  line
  line `(i) "landscape architect" means a person who deals with the design of open spaces relating to`
  line `plants, trees and landscape;`
  line
  line `(ii) "naval architect" means an architect who deals with design and construction of ships.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), he shall be punishable on first`
  line `conviction with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and on any subsequent conviction with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine not exceeding one thousand rupees or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (40798)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Failure to surrender certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40798&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `If any person whose name has been removed`
  line `from the register fails without sufficient cause forthwith to surrender his certificate of registration, he`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees, and, in the case of a continuing`
  line `failure, with an additional fine which may extend to ten rupees for each day after the first during which he`
  line `has persisted in the failure.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (40799)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40799&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act, except upon complaint made by order of the Council or a person authorised in this behalf by the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) No Magistrate other than a Presidency Magistrate or a Magistrate of the first class shall try any`
  line `offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (40800)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Information to be furnished by Council and publication thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40800&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall`
  line `furnish such reports, copies of its minutes, and other information to the Central Government as that`
  line `Government may require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may publish, in such manner as it may think fit, any report, copy or other`
  line `information furnished to it under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (40801)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40801&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, the Council or any member of the Council, the Executive Committee`
  line `or any other committee or officers and other employees of the Council for anything which is in good faith`
  line `done or intended to be done under this Act or any rule or regulation made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (40802)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Members of Council and officers and employees to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40802&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The members of the`
  line `Council and officers and other employees of the Council shall be deemed to be public servants within the`
  line `meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (40803)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40803&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the`
  line `date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament and the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 44 shall apply in respect of such`
  line `order as it applies in respect of a rule made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (40804)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40804&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which elections under Chapter II shall be conducted, the terms and conditions`
  line `of service of the member of the Tribunal appointed under sub-section (2) of section 5 and the`
  line `procedure to be followed by the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by the expert committee constituted under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 14 in the transaction of its business and the powers and duties of the expert`
  line `committee and the travelling and daily allowances payable to the members thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) the particulars to be included in the register of architects under sub-section (3) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which a certificate of registration is to be issued under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 24, sub-section (4) of section 26 and section 33;`
  line
  line `(e) the fee to be paid under sections 24, 25, 26, 27, 28, 32 and 33;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions on which name may be restored to the register under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of endorsement under sub-section (3) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which the Council shall hold an enquiry under section 30;`
  line
  line `(i) the fee for supplying printed copies of the register under section 34;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is to be or may be provided by rules under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may, be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `to the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (40805)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power of Council to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1982, s. 2 (w.e.f. 18-5-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770&sectionId=40805&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00017_197220_1517807324770
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, with the approval of the Central`
  line `Government, ^1[by notification in the Official Gazette], make regulations not inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act, or the rules made thereunder, to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the management of the property of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and duties of the President and the Vice-President of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) the summoning and holding of meetings of the Council and the Executive Committee or any`
  line `other committee constituted under section 10, the times and places at which such meetings shall be`
  line `held, the conduct of business thereat and the number of persons necessary to constitute a quorum;`
  line
  line `(d) the functions of the Executive Committee or of any other committee constituted under`
  line `section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the courses and periods of study and of practical training, if any, to be undertaken, the subjects`
  line `of examinations and standards of proficiency therein to be obtained in any college or institution for`
  line `grant of recognised qualifications;`
  line
  line `(f) the appointment, powers and duties of inspector;`
  line
  line `(g) the standards of staff, equipment, accommodation, training and other facilities for`
  line `architectural education;`
  line
  line `(h) the conduct of professional examinations, qualifications of examiners and the conditions of`
  line `admission to such examinations;`
  line
  line `(i) the standards of professional conduct and etiquette and code of ethics to be observed by`
  line architects;
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is to be or may be provided by regulations under this Act and in`
  line `respect of which no rules have been made.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Every regulation made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `वास्‍तुविद् अधिनियम, 1972`
